    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "ABOUT THE COMPANY\n\nThrill Labs is the driving force behind Thrill.com http://Thrill.com, an exciting new crypto gaming venture. We're focused on creating magical and immersive gaming experiences for a global audience. Our goal is to build a platform that resonates with millions, providing innovative gameplay and a vibrant community. Backed by a world-class team, we're committed to designing the next generation of engaging gaming experiences.\n\n\nTHE OPPORTUNITY\n\nAre you passionate about uncovering insights from data to drive strategic decisions? Do you thrive in fast-paced environments where you can have a real impact? If so, this is your opportunity to join Thrill Labs, where we are revolutionizing the gaming industry with data-driven innovation in crypto-powered entertainment.\n\nWe are looking for a Data Analyst to join our team and play a crucial role in extracting, analyzing, and visualizing key business insights. Your work will directly influence product development, customer experience, and operational strategies. By leveraging data, you’ll help shape the future of Thrill.com http://Thrill.com, making it a leading name in the industry.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\n - Data Analysis \u0026 Insights: Analyze complex datasets to extract actionable insights that drive product, marketing, and operational strategies.\n\n - Performance Monitoring: Develop and maintain dashboards and reports to track key business metrics.\n\n - Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with product, engineering, operations, marketing, and leadership teams to identify and solve critical business challenges.\n\n - Data Quality \u0026 Process Improvement: Ensure data integrity, optimise data pipelines, and contribute to improving internal analytics processes.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED\n\n - 6+ years of experience in a data analysis role. Leadership experience a plus.\n\n - Strong SQL skills, with experience querying large datasets.\n\n - Basic ETL skills\n\n - Proficiency in data visualization tools such as Looker, Tableau, or Power BI.\n\n - Experience with Google Analytics / customer behaviour tracking tools.\n\n - Strong analytical mindset, with the ability to translate data into actionable recommendations.\n\n - Excellent communication skills, with the ability to convey insights to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\n - Experience working autonomously in a fast-paced, start-up / scale-up environment.\n\n\nBONUS POINTS FOR\n\n - Experience in the iGaming industry (casino and sports betting).\n\n - Familiarity with blockchain analytics and on-chain data.\n\n - Experience working with ETL pipeline tools such as Clickhouse or Snowflake\n\n - Exposure to A/B testing frameworks and growth analytics.\n\n - Experience with Python or R for statistical analysis and data manipulation.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Thrill Labs, you'll be at the forefront of innovation in gaming, working with cutting-edge technology and a team of experts dedicated to pushing the boundaries of what's possible. This is not just another job—it’s a chance to shape the future of crypto gaming through data-driven decisions.\n\n🚀 Ready to make an impact? Apply now!",
